    {
      "id": "RQ-0049",
      "status": "todo",
      "title": "Investigate tracked queue and done staleness after best-effort coordinator refresh failures",
      "description": "Principles violated: J (consistency/integrity), G (least astonishment), H (operational hygiene). The successful worker-finish path tolerates coordinator branch refresh failures, and tracked queue/done files are explicitly excluded from workspace-to-source mirroring, so tracked source bookkeeping may stay stale whenever the local fast-forward step cannot run cleanly. Why it matters: operators can see a successful worker and updated remote branch while their local tracked queue/done files still show pre-integration state, which invites repeated work or incorrect manual recovery. Minimal fix if confirmed: either make tracked bookkeeping refresh explicit after a successful worker push or surface a blocking error when the source branch cannot be refreshed cleanly. Acceptance criteria: a focused regression or temp harness proves whether tracked source queue/done can stay stale after a successful worker completion with refresh failure; go if stale local bookkeeping persists, no-go if source files are already refreshed or the flow correctly blocks.",
      "priority": "medium",
      "tags": [
        "maintenance",
        "parallel",
        "investigate"
      ],
      "scope": [
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/events.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/mod.rs",
        "crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/events.rs::tests"
      ],
      "evidence": [
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/events.rs:115-117 and 180-187 :: successful worker completion only does a best-effort fast-forward refresh before syncing bookkeeping back to source",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/sync/mod.rs:80-85 and 158-166 :: tracked queue/done files are left to git branch updates and are never mirrored back from the workspace on success",
        "path: crates/ralph/src/commands/run/parallel/orchestration/events.rs:438-467 :: finished_success_tolerates_branch_refresh_failure proves success is still reported when coordinator refresh fails, but there is no assertion that tracked source bookkeeping stays current"
      ],
      "plan": [
        "Build a focused temp-repo repro where queue/done are tracked, worker completion succeeds, and local coordinator refresh is forced to fail.",
        "Observe whether the local tracked queue/done files remain stale even though the worker success path returns Ok and remote integration succeeds.",
        "If confirmed, implement explicit tracked bookkeeping refresh or promote the refresh failure to a surfaced operator-facing failure path.",
        "Verify by adding a regression for the forced-refresh-failure scenario and confirming the local source queue/done files are either refreshed or the run surfaces a blocking error instead of silently succeeding."
      ],
